node.text:
MY TOP 5 TIPS ON HOW TO FIND SUCCESS AS A CONSULTANT / COACH... 

Alright... bad news for 90% of "online coaches & consultants" out there giving "professional & the best" advice... statistics show and prove that it takes 10,000 hours+ to be an ACTUAL professional or MASTER anything. 

While these 16, 17, 18, 19 & 20 year olds might have some good tips and some YouTube videos under their belt, make sure you're talking to and paying a vetted professional who's been in your industry for 3+ years, and verify their success before fulfilling any invoice they send you. 

Here's my top 5 tips for finding massive success as a coach in your industry: 

1)	Become obsessed with your industry - when you become obsessed with your industry, you start learning the small things about it that make a huge difference. You're also going to have zero to very little success in your industry if you aren't obsessed with it. The grass is always greener where you water it. Water your work in your industry and you'll see the rewards. 

2)	Network with 20 people a day from your industry - this builds knowledge, social credibility and increased opportunity for you within your industry / niche. 

3)	Find your USP (unique selling position) - Think like a fish, not a fisherman. Sounds dumb, but this really works. Where do the majority of the fish (potential clients) hang out? Fish from the clients point of view, not yours. 

4)	Stay consistent and over-serve - People follow people that KNOW where they are going. How do people know where you're going? When you're consistent, fired up and over-serving... people know you're going somewhere and doing something. Oh, and when people pay for $5,000 worth of service, give them $7,000 worth of services. Client retention low? Probably because you're lacking somewhere. 

5)	Beta-test clients before taking on real clients - Make sure your services work and generate impressive / consistent revenue before charging people. Nobody likes leaving you empty handed or with false expectations. You'll be a top 1% coach if anyone can come to you and anyone can leave wealthier than when they came.

node.text:
LET'S TALK LEADERSHIP... 

A HUGE part of having a successful business whether it's online or brick & mortar is leadership! 

Why? 

Because, everything rises and falls on leadership. There's no "I" in team. Cliche saying, it' still stands true in every scenario. 

Before you can lead others you must lead yourself, then others will follow. 

That being said, let's get deeper here. That's what you're in this mastermind for...

A man or woman who has faced their demons and has fully healed is the most equipped to SERVE and LEAD others. 

You heard it, do NOT avoid problems in your personal or business life. 

Problems = Money 

Business revolves around solving problems. If you equip yourself daily to solve problems, it will be second nature in business and the activity of solving problems will be a money machine. 

I challenge you this week, doesn't matter if the problems are small or large... to face them head on and to NOT push them away. Find a solution immediately. 

Business is about offering solutions to the markets problems. 

I have a private Facebook community for people that want to learn HOW!
 
Make sure to join our private Facebook community by using the link in my profile!

Let’s get to 7 figures!🚀

node.text:
Had to come to Russia to secure the big bag 💼 

Having a international business that I am running in every country around the world is one of the biggest blessings on the planet! Any time of day I have wires, deposits, commissions and recurring payments coming in while I’m traveling. If you aren’t making 1-5k a day then message me “coach” to schedule a coaching call! No time wasters or people who have to question the investment. I don’t have time for these kind of people! 

Let’s build passive income streams for you and your family starting today!

node.text:
📌 Pinning comments leads to Instagram Sales
⠀
Essentially, you can pin comments to the top of your post so people that view the post will see those comments first.
⠀
🤔 Why? - This feature will give you more control over what the conversation looks like on your posts. The aim is to try and drive more positive conversation within the comment section!
⠀
🗣 Which comments should you pin? - Totally up to you but try and pin a mix of comments rather than all very similar! We would recommend pinning comments that will genuinely help consumers rather than pinning the most positive ones. For example, if there’s a good question that someone asks in the comments, pin this comment so that your reply is at the top and new consumers won’t have to go searching for answers!
⠀
❓How do I pin this comment? - All you have to do is swipe left on the comment you want to pin, and select the pin icon - easy peasy!
⠀
📲 Will they be notified? YES! - the person who’s comment you pin will receive a notification to inform them! ✨ How many can I pin?
⠀
Up to three! So choose wisely 🤓

node.text:
Struggling Facebook ad campaigns? 🤔

There are a few common mistakes that so many people make that could be hurting
your ad performance:

Did you know that your performance only reaches optimal level after exiting the learning phase?

Patience is key 🔑 Every time you make a change to a campaign, i.e change the budget, tweak a creative... it re-sets the learning phase! An ad set needs to receive 50 conversations in 7 days to exit the learning phase, so ideally you shouldn’t be making any changes to a new campaign as it’s running through your learning phase!

Too many ads or ad sets 🥵 having too many ads or ad sets in your campaigns can burn up your cash quick. Your ad sets will struggle to drive conversions and exit the learning phase! Consolidate your campaigns to include as few ad sets as possible, and aim to have only 3-5 ads per ad set.

Too few ads 🥶 similarly, too few ads can ice your ad performance! Having too few ads in an ad set will cause the ad to experience ‘ad fatigue’ quicker. As well, it’s always best to have multiple variations of ad creative and copy! 

You can never be sure which will resonate with your audience the best and drive performance, and what appeals to one consumer may not appeal to another. So having variations will allow Facebook to optimise towards the one that drives the most conversions! 📈

Did you find this post helpful? Make sure you click save so you can refer back to it. 💫

node.text:
Small businesses SUCK at Instagram 😲

They know they need it but they don’t really know how to utilize it to generate actual revenue for the business! 🆘

This can be due to many reasons, but one of them is because they don’t know about
all the features that are available to them as a business ✨

I am hoping this post will help (so you might want to save it) 🔖

Before doing anything, you should convert your account to an Instagram business account. You can do this under Settings > Account > Switch to business account 🌟

Once you have a business account you have a host of features available to you to help you grow your business and make sales (swipe to see a few of them) 🤭

As a small business it can be overwhelming to have so many options and seem difficult to choose which you should be using. But, the best way to find out is to research each tool and try them out 🙌

Do you have any questions about any of these features? Ask away in the comments below 💬
